CASE
  WHEN <condition-1> THEN <Result-1>
  WHEN <condition-2> THEN <Result-2>
........
  ELSE <result- else part>
END

Note :- if else part is not defined in CASE statement & any of the condition not met then it populates NULL

example-1 :- CASE 
              WHEN sales>50 THEN 'high' 
              WHEN sales>30 THEN 'Medium'
            ELSE 'low'
            END

case statement is used for Data Transformation ==> Derive new information ==> create new columns based on existing data.

Use Case:- Categorization of data.

SELECT CATEGORY,SUM(sales) SUM_OF_SALES FROM
(
SELECT
OrderID,
Sales,
CASE WHEN Sales>50 THEN 'High'
     WHEN Sales>30 THEN 'Medium'
     ELSE 'Low'
     END CATEGORY
FROM 
Sales.Orders
)t
GROUP BY CATEGORY
ORDER BY SUM_OF_SALES desc


CASE RULES ---Always return result should of same datatype.

SELECT 
FirstName,
Gender,
CASE WHEN Gender='M' THEN 'Male'
     WHEN Gender='F' THEN 'Female'
     ELSE 'N/A'
     END 'GENDER_Abbreviation',
CASE Gender WHEN 'M' THEN 'Male'
            WHEN 'F' THEN 'Female'
            ELSE 'N/A'
            END 'Gender_Abbreviation2'
FROM 
Sales.Employees

